comments.body:
Narrowed down the issue to an exception being raised when looking for an instance type in the Predefined enum list... This is the line causing the exception causing the reset failure:

{code}
              PredefinedTypes defaultVmType = PredefinedTypes.valueOf( vmTypeName );
{code}

Used the following script to reset all instance types, launched and terminated a few instances, then modified the instance types and launched more instances. No issues found.

{code}
for type in `euca-describe-instance-types  | grep -v Name | awk '{print $2}'`;do euca-modify-instance-type --reset $type; done
{code}
